DevName.description: API name of the chart. This name can contain only underscores and alphanumeric characters, and must be unique in your org. It must begin with a letter, not include spaces, not end with an underscore, and not contain two consecutive underscores. In managed packages, this field prevents naming conflicts on package installations. With this field, a developer can change the object’s name in a managed package and the changes are reflected in a subscriber’s organization.

ExternalId.description: A unique system-generated numerical identifier for the user.

HelpLocator.description: The URL for the help page.

Locator.description: The aura component list (aura page) or page URL (aloha page).

NetworkID.description: The ID of the Experience Cloud site.

PageType.description: Type of page accessed within Experience Workspaces.

Parent.description: The devName of the parent node.

Workspace.description: The devName of the workspace the node belongs to.
